/(Root): This is the base of the Linux directory, every directory arises from the root directory
         (Starting point of File system Hierarchy).

/root: Home directory for the root user(Superuser).

/bin(User Binaries : Commands used by all the users of the system are located here.(Contains binary executables).

/sbin(System Binaries): Commands located under this directory are used by system administrator.
                       (for system maiintainence purpose-(iptables,reboot,fdisk,ifconfig,swapon))

/dev(Device Files): Contains hardware device files,include terminal devices,usb or any device attached to the system.

/var(Variable Files): Variable data files(File contents that tend to grow)such as log files are located here.
          -/var/log: System log files generated by OS and other applications.
          -/var/lib: Contains database and package files.
          -/var/mail: Contains Emails.
          -/var/tmp: Contains Temporary files needed for reboot.

/mnt(Mount Directory): Used to mount a file system temporarily.

/media: Contains subdirectories where removable media devices inserted into the computer are mounted.

/usr(User Binaries): Contains applications and files used by users.

/etc: Contains all configurations files of server.
      Controls the behavior of an operating system or application.
      Contains startup and shutdown program scripts used to start or stop individual programs.

/boot: Files neededto boot the system are located(GRUB boot loaders files and Linux kernels are stored here).

/opt(Optional Applications): This directory is used for installing the application software from third party vendors
                             that are not available in the linux distribution.  
           Usually, the software code is stored in the opt directory and the binary code is linked to the bin directory
           so that all users can run that software.

/home: Contains secondary users home directory.

/tmp: Contains temporary files created by system and users.
      Files in this directory are deleted when system is rebooted.
                   

























